# Wasm El Seba — Automation (Simple)

Lightweight Selenium + TestNG automation for the Wasm El Seba website.

## Quick start
1. Clone:
   git clone https://github.com/mohamedbarakat24/wasm_el_seba_automation.git
2. Enter folder:
   cd wasm_el_seba_automation
3. Run all tests:
   mvn clean test

Run in headless (CI-like) mode:
- Unix/macOS: CI=true mvn test
- Windows PowerShell: $env:CI='true'; mvn test

## Theme (UI)
Tests can run against different UI themes (light / dark) if the site supports it.

- Default: light theme.
- To run with dark theme (if your tests/pages support a theme flag), pass a Maven property:
  mvn -Dtheme=dark test

You can also set THEME in GitHub Actions job env:
```yaml
env:
  CI: true
  THEME: dark
```

(If your tests need a specific action to switch theme, add a small helper in your BaseTest or page objects that applies the theme before running assertions.)

## Debugging tips
- If tests pass locally but fail in CI:
  - Run locally in headless: CI=true mvn test
  - Capture screenshots and page source on failure
  - Increase waits for slow UI elements (OTP modals, toasts)

## Project layout (short)
- src/main/java — pages, locators, helpers
- src/test/java — tests, BaseTest, listeners
- testng.xml — suite config
- .github/workflows/run-tests.yml — CI workflow

## Contact
Open an issue in this repo for help or improvements.
